{
  "name": "leios_vote_for_unannounced_eb",
  "description": "The server sends one legitimate vote batch for EB1 (hash=ab..), which was properly advertised via block_offer. It then sends a second batch referencing an EB that was never announced or offered in this session (hash=ef..). A conforming node must track which EBs it has been made aware of before counting votes toward them. Accepting votes for an unseen EB would allow a malicious peer to pre-accumulate phantom vote tallies for blocks that may never arrive, or to correlate vote batches with block deliveries from a different peer. The verifier should observe the node flagging the second batch as referencing an unknown EB.",
  "network_magic": 42,
  "trace_output_path": "trace_leios_vote_for_unannounced_eb.jsonl",
